data.enText: a short summary or account of sth

data.chText: 到目前为止事件的概述
data.enText: a brief résumé of events so far
if you resume an activity, or if it resumes , it begins again or continues after an interruption

data.chText: 重新进行会谈 / 谈判
经过六年的间歇之后她又重新上岗。
data.enText: She resumed her career after an interval of six years.
The noise resumed, louder than before.
He got back in the car and resumed driving.

data.chText: 恢复席位 / 地位 / 职位
data.enText: to go back to the seat or place that you had before

word_means: 恢复席位 / 地位 / 职位
simple_means.memory_skill: re 重新 + sum 拿，取 + e → 重新拿起 → 恢复

means: 恢复席位 / 地位 / 职位

ex.enText: She kept walking in the garden.
The boy kept asking me questions.

synonyms.bx: 指继续做之前所做的某事或重复做同一件事。

ex.chText: 这个婴儿一晚上都在哭。
ex.enText: The baby continued to cry all night.
He continued to work after he recovered.

ex.chText: 晚饭后我们继续下国际象棋如何？
ex.enText: Shall we continue playing chess after supper?

synonyms.bx: 指持续而不停止，也可指中断后又继续下去。

ex.chText: 噪声24个小时没有消停过。
ex.enText: The noise went on for 24 hours.

ex.chText: 他不应该这样生活下去了。
ex.enText: He oughtn't to go on living this way.

ex.chText: 巴辛接着给我们讲了些别的东西。
ex.enText: Bassin went on to tell us something different.

synonyms.bx: 指不停顿地继续下去；go on doing sth 表示继续干同一件事，而 go on to do sth 则表示干完一件事后接着干另一件事。

ex.chText: 两天以后，他们继续旅行。
ex.enText: Two days later, they resumed their journey.

ex.chText: 幕间休息之后，那位小提琴手又重新开始演奏。
ex.enText: The violinist resumed playing after the intermission.

tr: a summary of your academic and work history
return to a previous location or condition
example: The painting resumed its old condition when we restored it

value.def: If you resume an activity or if it resumes, it begins again.

example.ex: After the war he resumed his duties at Emmanuel College...
example.tran: 战争过后，他重新开始了在伊曼纽尔学院的工作。

example.ex: The search is expected to resume early today.
example.tran: 预计搜寻工作会于今天早些时候重新开始。

example.ex: It is premature to speculate about the resumption of negotiations.
example.tran: 现在猜测谈判是否会重新开始还为时过早。

value.def: If you resume your seat or position, you return to the seat or position you were in before you moved.

example.ex: 'I changed my mind,' Blanche said, resuming her seat.
example.tran: “我改变主意了，”布兰奇说着回到她的座位上。

value.def: If someone resumes, they begin speaking again after they have stopped for a short time.

example.ex: 'Hey, Judith,' he resumed, 'tell me all about yourself.'
example.tran: “嘿，朱迪思，”他接着说，“跟我谈谈你自己吧。”

trans: 以学历为主；以学历为主的简历
